'''
# Assertions - means debugging purpose, we use
# we can use assertions alternate as print statement
# debugs means checking excepeted output if not come we need to fix the bug
# the process of identifying bug and fixing the bug is called debugging
# ADVANTAGES OF ASSERATIONS
# 1> no need to remove assert statement
# 2> we can enable asseration and desiable asseration statement
types of assert statements two
1> simple version=
assert conditional_expression(it will check the condition right or wrong  )
Example below

2> very simple version(Augmented version)

'''
no=10



#assert no>10     # simple version

assert no>10,'Here no should be >10 but not comming'  # Augmented version

# assertion statement
